Essex Chemical Corp said it filed withthe Securities and Exchange Commission a registration statementcovering a 60 mln dlr issue of convertivble subordinateddebentures due 2012.    Proceeds will be used to redeem the company's outstanding11-3/8 pct subordinated debentures due 1998 and repay all longand short-term notes payable to banks, as well as for workingcapital, Essex Chemical said.    The company named Thomson McKinnon Securities Inc as leadmanager and PaineWebber Inc as co-manager of the offering. Reuter&#3;